<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-09T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="869" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d869">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12787.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Vice Consul <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-09T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 9, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Brazilian Minister cables requesting Department to transmit to Carranza’s
                            Secretary of War the following:</p>
                        <p>[Quotes the message contained in the Minster’s No. 119, August 8.]</p>
                        <p>Please bring this to the immediate attention of General Carranza and urge
                            upon him the importance of continuing negotiations in a <pb facs="0700" n="584" xml:id="pg_584"/> conciliatory spirit until a basis is
                            reached for the peaceful transfer of authority. We feel confident
                            President Carbajal will agree to any reasonable conditions. Department
                            will gladly transmit Carranza’s reply.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>